commit.message:
Bump pwx for v255.4 last commit data

Signed-off-by: Sven Eden <sven@eden-worx.com>

Change RLIM_FMT to '%llu' for non-glibc builds (#269)

Musl libc does not differentiate between 32-bit builds and 64-builds
any more when defining rlim_t and just typedefs it to
'unsigned long long'.
Therefore using '%ju' as a format string no longer works on 64-bit
builds due to the superfluous 'long'.

But as it is now fixed on one type, we can use '%llu' instead.

Bug: #269
Closes: #269
Signed-off-by: Sven Eden <sven@eden-worx.com>

Bug: #263
Closes: #263
Signed-off-by: Sven Eden <sven@eden-worx.com>

test-cgroup: Skip when run in minimal containers (#261)

If elogind is built in a minimal container, cg_unified_cached() might
return -ENOENT instead of -ENOMEDIUM.

Bug: #261
Signed-off-by: Sven Eden <sven@eden-worx.com>

Utilize PRI formats so building on 32bit no longer fails (#252)

Signed-off-by: Sven Eden <sven@eden-worx.com>

Use the same method to write to nvidia suspend, as to sleep state.

Signed-off-by: Sven Eden <sven@eden-worx.com>

Fork out for performing power/sleep operations (#234)

systemd starts individual processes to reboot or suspend a machine,
like systemd-sleep for example.

Some operations need to communicate with elogind via dbus, which is
not possible while elogind is performing the operation by itself.

All operations that reboot, poweroff, suspend or hibernate the
machine are now forked off, so the operation can communicate with
elogind from the outside.

Many thanks to @rsauex for coming up with this idea!

Bug: #234
Closes: #234
